1. Introduction

This document defines the complete technology stack for Sentix Tinder — a mobile-first sentiment analysis platform that processes Tinder app store reviews and presents NLP-derived insights through an interactive dashboard. It covers every layer of the system: data ingestion, machine learning model training, backend API, frontend UI, infrastructure, and the Kaggle competition workflow.

The project is explicitly designed around production-grade ML frameworks — scikit-learn for baseline modelling, PyTorch and TensorFlow/Keras for deep learning, and HuggingFace Transformers for BERT-based fine-tuning. Kaggle is used both as a dataset source and as a competition/benchmarking platform.

1.1 Architectural Layers
#	Layer	Responsibility
L1	ML / NLP Core	Data preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, evaluation, inference
L2	Backend API	Serve model predictions, expose REST endpoints, manage pipeline orchestration
L3	Frontend Dashboard	React mobile UI: Dashboard, Aspect Analysis, Review Explorer, Keyword Insights
L4	Data & Storage	Review collection, preprocessing, structured storage, versioning
L5	Dev / MLOps	Environment management, experiment tracking, CI/CD, model registry

