3. Machine Learning Framework Deep Dive

This section details exactly how each major ML framework is used within the Sentix Tinder pipeline, with justification for each choice and the specific pipeline stage it powers.

3.1 scikit-learn — Baseline & Classical ML
Version	scikit-learn 1.4.x
Role in Project	Baseline sentiment classifier, TF-IDF feature extraction, model evaluation, spam detection
Install	pip install scikit-learn

Usage Details
•TfidfVectorizer: converts cleaned review text into TF-IDF sparse feature matrices (max_features=50,000, ngram_range=(1,2))
•MultinomialNB: Naïve Bayes baseline for 2-class sentiment (Positive / Negative)
•LogisticRegression: second baseline with L2 regularisation; typically outperforms NB on review data
•LinearSVC: fast linear SVM, strong F1 score on longer reviews, used as the production classical model
•GridSearchCV / RandomizedSearchCV: hyperparameter tuning with 5-fold stratified cross-validation
•classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score: evaluation metrics piped to MLflow logging
•cosine_similarity (from sklearn.metrics.pairwise): spam/duplicate detection by pairwise TF-IDF similarity

Expected Performance (Baseline)
Model	Accuracy	Precision	Recall	Macro F1
Naïve Bayes + TF-IDF	~74%	~72%	~71%	~0.71
Logistic Regression + TF-IDF	~79%	~78%	~77%	~0.77
LinearSVC + TF-IDF	~81%	~80%	~79%	~0.79

3.2 PyTorch — Deep Learning Backbone
Version	PyTorch 2.2.x  (CUDA 12.1 build for GPU training)
Role in Project	BERT fine-tuning, custom classification head, training loop management, model serialisation
Install	pip install torch torchvision  (or conda install pytorch -c pytorch)

Usage Details
•torch.utils.data.Dataset: wraps review DataFrames into tokenised PyTorch datasets for the DataLoader
•DataLoader: batched loading with shuffle=True for training, shuffle=False for eval
•AutoModelForSequenceClassification (via HuggingFace): loads bert-base-uncased with a 2-class head
•AdamW optimiser with linear warmup schedule (transformers.get_linear_schedule_with_warmup)
•Mixed-precision training via torch.cuda.amp.autocast for faster Kaggle GPU utilisation
•torch.save / torch.load: checkpoint saves every epoch; best checkpoint selected by val F1
•torch.nn.functional.softmax: converts logits to per-class probability scores surfaced in the API response

Training Configuration (BERT)
Parameter	Value
Base model	bert-base-uncased (110M params)
Max sequence length	128 tokens (review texts are short; 256 for longer comparisons)
Batch size	32 (training) / 64 (evaluation)
Learning rate	2e-5 with linear warmup over 10% of steps
Epochs	4 (early stopping on val loss, patience=2)
Optimiser	AdamW (weight_decay=0.01)
Label smoothing	0.1 on cross-entropy loss
Expected Macro F1	≥ 0.85 on held-out test set

3.3 TensorFlow / Keras — Prototyping & Export
Version	TensorFlow 2.16.x  (Keras 3 included)
Role in Project	LSTM/GRU baseline, Keras-native BERT via TFBertForSequenceClassification, TFLite export
Install	pip install tensorflow  (GPU: pip install tensorflow[and-cuda])

Usage Details
•tf.keras.preprocessing.text.Tokenizer + pad_sequences: token-level preprocessing for LSTM baseline
•tf.keras.Sequential LSTM/BiGRU model: word-embedding → BiGRU(128) → Dense(64) → Softmax(2)
•TFBertForSequenceClassification: TensorFlow version of BERT, used to cross-validate PyTorch fine-tuning results
•tf.saved_model.save: exports the fine-tuned model for serving via TF Serving or conversion to TFLite for mobile
•TF-Lite conversion (tf.lite.TFLiteConverter): optional on-device inference path for future mobile SDK integration
•tf.data.Dataset: efficient data pipeline with .cache().shuffle().batch().prefetch() for fast training I/O

3.4 HuggingFace Transformers — Pre-trained Model Hub
Model Selection
Model ID	Use Case	Why Chosen
bert-base-uncased	Primary classifier	Strong general-purpose text encoder; well-studied on app review corpora
distilbert-base-uncased	Fast inference API	40% smaller, 60% faster than BERT, retains 97% of accuracy
