8. Environment Setup Guide

8.1 Python / ML Environment
•Python 3.11+ recommended (3.10 minimum for PyTorch 2.x compatibility)
•Create a virtual environment: python -m venv .venv  →  source .venv/bin/activate
•Install ML dependencies: pip install torch transformers datasets scikit-learn spacy nltk pandas numpy mlflow optuna
•Install API dependencies: pip install fastapi uvicorn pydantic celery redis onnxruntime
•Download spaCy model: python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm
•Download NLTK data: python -c "import nltk; nltk.download('stopwords'); nltk.download('wordnet')"

8.2 Kaggle Setup
•Create a Kaggle account and generate an API key from Account → API → Create New Token
•Place kaggle.json at ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json and set permissions: chmod 600 ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json
•Install the Kaggle CLI: pip install kaggle
•Verify: kaggle --version

8.3 Frontend Setup
•Node.js 20 LTS required
•cd dashboard && npm install
•Development server: npm run dev  (Vite, hot reload at localhost:5173)
•Production build: npm run build  (outputs to dashboard/dist/)

8.4 Docker Compose (Full Stack)
•docker compose up --build  — starts API (port 8000), Redis (6379), and Celery worker
•API is accessible at http://localhost:8000/docs (auto-generated Swagger UI from FastAPI)



