10. Technology Decision Rationale

Decision	Chosen	Alternatives Considered
Primary DL framework	PyTorch 2.2	TensorFlow 2.x — both are used, but PyTorch is primary for BERT due to HuggingFace Trainer API depth
API framework	FastAPI	Flask — chosen FastAPI for automatic OpenAPI docs, async support, and Pydantic v2 integration
Frontend framework	React + Vite	Next.js — Vite chosen for simpler SPA setup matching the mobile prototype; no SSR needed
Classical ML library	scikit-learn	No serious alternative — scikit-learn is the standard for TF-IDF, SVM, and pipeline management
Chart library	Chart.js (+ Recharts)	D3.js — Chart.js matched existing Stitch prototype code exactly; Recharts added for React-native components
Local storage	SQLite	PostgreSQL — SQLite chosen for zero-config local development; swap to PostgreSQL for production
Model inference speed	ONNX Runtime	Torch native — ONNX provides 3–5× faster CPU inference for the deployed API endpoint
Styling system	Tailwind CSS 3.4	CSS Modules / styled-components — Tailwind directly mirrors the Stitch prototype utility classes


